canonical:
  title: 夜坐
  author: 李冑
  language: lzh
  text: 陰風慘慘雨淋淋海氣連山石竇深此夜浮生餘白首點燈時復顧初心
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 夜坐
  author: 李冑
  language: lzh
  text: 陰風慘慘雨淋淋。海氣連山石竇深。此夜浮生餘白首。點燈時復顧初心。
korean:
  title: 야좌
  author: 이주
  language: kor
  text: |-
    음풍은 쌀쌀하고 비는 임림할 제
    바다 기운 메를 잇고 돌구멍은 깊었어라
    이날 밤 부생이 흰 머리만 남았는데
    등불 켜고 때로 다시 옛 마음을 돌보았네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0390&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Night Sitting
  author: Lee Ju
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The bitter wind blows chill, the rain falls grey—
    Sea mist clings to the mountain, stone caves run deep.
    This night, of fleeting life, only white hair remains;
    I light the lamp and recall, once more, my youthful heart.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 浮生 (floating life) refers to the transient nature of human existence, a Buddhist-influenced concept common in East Asian poetry
  - key: ''
    value: The image of white hair contrasts with the rekindled memory of one's youthful aspirations, capturing the melancholy of aging and the bittersweet return to earlier ideals
